description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band: 3 Administrator / Co-ordinator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours: 30hrs over 5 days a week (7month fixed term)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Location: Heartlands Hospital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a fixed term contract for a period of 7 months. We are looking for an enthusiastic, self-motivated individual to provide administrative and clerical support to our well established cardiac rehabilitation service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should hold a qualification in Business Administration NVQ level 3 or have equivalent experience in an administrative environment. They should be able to demonstrate excellent IT skills including Microsoft Office and Excel Spreadsheets. Experience in the use of databases is desirable and knowledge of Ultragenda and digital dictation would be beneficial but not essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to prioritise and self-manage their workload is essential. An excellent telephone manner to deal with patients and staff enquiries is important at all times.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like further information about this post please contact either Sr Catherine McIlduff on 0121 424 2000, bleep 2915 or Sr Rachel Robins on 0121 424 2902.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date: Wednesday 25th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
